Starting an App using Expo

Type in terminal: 

npx create-expo-app WeatherApp

navigate to project folder then type in npm start

scan QR code


Open Expo Go app on phone

Then open project in VS code and start project!



you need to install eslint:
npm install esline --save -dev
npx eslint --init




then,

npm install @react-native-community/eslint-config --save-dev















Install Prettier:

npm install --save-dev --save-exact prettier




create a file for the config for prettier in root project directory

touch .prettierrc.js







https://prettier.io/docs/en/configuration.html
.prettierrc.js:

module.exports = {
  arrowParens: 'avoid',
  bracketSameLine: true,
  bracketSpacing: true,
  singleQuote: true,
  trailingComma: 'none',
  tabWidth: 2,
  useTabs: false,
  semi: false
};










Add eslint script in package.json:

"lint": "eslint. "

in terminal: eslint run lint























